[SN]TITLE[SN]
James Attfield murder: Victim's mum lost job during trial

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The mother of a man murdered by a Yorkshire Ripper-obsessed teen has told how she lost her job during the trial.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
James Attfield, 33, was knifed to death by the then 15-year-old James Fairweather in Colchester in 2014.
Fairweather, who went on to murder 31-year-old Saudi Arabian student Nahid Almanea three months later, is now serving a double life prison sentence.
Julie Finch, 53, told the BBC how, after the trauma of her son's death, she had also lost her job and home.
